{"@context": "http://schema.org", "@type": "Recipe", "name": "Watermelon & Tomato Salsa", "description": "Sweet, juicy watermelon and spicy chiles combine to create a surprising summer salsa with a kick. It goes especially well with grilled fish. Watermelon is a refreshing ingredient to use in a salsa. I\u2019ve combined it with tomatoes and jicama here, and the result is a fruity/vegetal salsa with a kick from chiles, lime and cilantro. Like the other fruit-based salsas I\u2019m featuring this week, I like this with rilled fish, especially light-fleshed fish like halibut or mahi-mahi.", "author": {"@type": "Person", "name": "Martha Rose Shulman"}, "image": "https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/07/29/science/01recipehealth/01recipehealth-articleLarge.jpg", "totalTime": "PT30M", "recipeYield": "Makes 3 cups", "recipeCuisine": "mexican", "recipeCategory": "breakfast, brunch, dinner, lunch, sauces and gravies, appetizer, side dish", "keywords": "", "aggregateRating": {"@type": "AggregateRating", "ratingValue": 4, "ratingCount": 39}, "nutrition": {"@context": "http://schema.org", "@type": "NutritionInformation", "calories": 23, "unsaturatedFatContent": "0 grams", "carbohydrateContent": "6 grams", "cholesterolContent": null, "fatContent": "0 grams", "fiberContent": "1 gram", "proteinContent": "1 gram", "saturatedFatContent": "0 grams", "sodiumContent": "210 milligrams", "sugarContent": "3 grams", "transFatContent": null}, "recipeIngredient": ["2 cups finely diced watermelon (about 6 ounces)", "1 cup finely chopped tomatoes (about 1/2 pound)", "3/4 cup finely diced jicama", "1 to 2 serrano chiles, minced (to taste)", "Salt to taste", "1 to 2 tablespoons fresh lime juice (to taste)", "1 to 2 tablespoons fresh lime juice (to taste)"], "recipeInstructions": [{"@context": "http://schema.org", "@type": "HowToStep", "text": "Combine all the ingredients in a medium bowl and stir together. Let sit for 15 to 30 minutes before serving."}], "isAccessibleForFree": "False", "hasPart":